                    <section id="aboutModalText">
                        <h2>History of SIWES</h2><br>
                        <p id="modalParagraph">
                            The Student Industrial Work Experience Scheme (SIWES) was Establish in 1973 by Industrial Training Fund (ITF) it is a very important program , involving the student, 
                            University, Industries, it is skill training program design to expose an prepare student of tertiary institution for the industrial work situations the are likely to meet after graduation.
                        </p><br>
                        <hr>
                        <br>

                        <h2>Aims and Objectives of SIWES</h2><br>
                        <p>The objectives of the studentâ€™s industrial work experience scheme [SIWES] are as follows:</p>
                        <ul class="aboutModalList">
                            <li>To expose students to work methods and technique in handling equipment and machinery that may not be available in the universities</li>
                            <li>To prepare students for the work situation they are likely to meet after graduation.</li>
                            <li>To provide an avenue for Nigerian universities to acquire industrial skills and experience in their course of study.</li>
                            <li>To provide students with an opportunity to apply their theoretical knowledge in real work situation there by bridging the gap between university work and actual practice.</li>
                            <li>To make the transition from the university to the world of work easier and thus, enhance students contacts for later job placement.</li>
                        </ul><br>
                        <hr>
                        <br>
                        <h2>Bodies Involved in the Management of SIWES</h2><br>
                        <ul class="aboutModalList">
                            <li>The Federal Government (FG).</li>
                            <li>Industrial Training Fund (ITF).</li>
                            <li>National University Commission (NUC).</li>
                            <li>The institution (universities).</li>
                        </ul>

                        <br>
                        <ul class="aboutModalList">
                            <li>
                                <span class="orderedListHeaders">The Federal Government</span>
                                <ol class="aboutModalOrderedList">
                                    <li>Makes adequate fund available to the Federal Ministry of Industry to fund the scheme.</li>
                                    <li>Make it mandatory for all Ministries, Companies and Government Parastatal to offer attachment places to students. </li>
                                    <li>Make it a policy to include a clause in every major contract lasting over six to nine months being awarded for contract to take students on attachment.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>

                            <br>
                            <li>
                                <span class="orderedListHeaders">Industrial Training Fund</span>
                                <ol class="aboutModalOrderedList">
                                    <li>Provide logistic materiel needed to administer the scheme.</li>
                                    <li>Compile lists of employers and available training places for industrial attachment and 	forward such lists to the coordinating Agencies. i.e. NUC, NBTE, NCCE.</li>
                                    <li>Organize biennial conferences and seminars on SIWES.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>

                            <br>
                            <li>
                                <span class="orderedListHeaders">National University Commission</span>
                                <ol class="aboutModalOrderedList">
                                    <li>Establish SIWES coordinating Units.</li>
                                    <li>Appoint full time coordinators to operate the scheme at agency level.</li>
                                    <li>Evolve a minimum national guide programme for supervised industrial training activities for approved courses.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>

                            <br>
                            <li>
                                <span class="orderedListHeaders">The Institutions (Universities)</span>
                                <ol class="aboutModalOrderedList">
                                    <li>Establish SIWES coordinating units and appoint Department/Faculty SIWES coordinators within the institutions.</li>
                                    <li>Appoint full-time Industrial Coordinators to operate the scheme at institutional level.</li>
                                    <li>Prepare and submit Master and placement to the respective coordinating agency and 	ITF.</li>
                                    <li>Place students on attachment with employee.</li>
                                    <li>Organize orientation program for students to prepare them for industrial training. ITF representative may be invited to give a talk to the students during the orientation 	programme.</li>
                                    <li>Work out industrial tailor-made program with the employers based supervisor on the 	National Industrial Training guideline for such course.</li>
                                    <li>Supervise students on attachment and sign their logbooks. A minimum three visits should be made to the students by the institution's supervisor during the period of attachment.</li>
                                    <li>Assess student's performance and award grades accordingly.</li>
                                    <li>Submit completed ITF Form 8 to the ITF at the end of the program.</li>
                                    <li>Maintain separate account books on the scheme to the ITF after the program.</li>
                                </ol>
                            </li>
                            
                        </ul>
